&gt;  Hi Selva,
&gt;  I&#39;ve not been paying attention so somebody might have already said this.
&gt;  Is the message you&#39;re getting similar to:
&gt;  BUILD FAILED: C:&#92;sandbox&#92;code&#92;build&#92;build.xml:199: Could not create task or
&gt; type of type: junit.
&gt;  
&gt;  If so you need to explicitly inform Ant within Eclipse where junit.jar is. 
&gt; Do this by bringing up the Eclipse Ant configuration dialog (context menu
&gt; &quot;Run Ant...&quot; on your xml file).  Go to the classpath tab and add an entry
&gt; for junit.jar (via &quot;Add JARS...&quot;, or &quot;Add External JARS...&quot; button)
&gt;  
&gt;  Jonathan
&gt;  
&gt;  ________________________________________
