&gt;  Sent: 11 March 2005 15:48
&gt;  To: junit@yahoogroups.com
&gt;  Subject: RE: [junit] Ant could not create task : junit
&gt; 
&gt;  
&gt;  
&gt;  &gt; I had problems running junit task and had to keep the junit jar
&gt;  &gt; (junit3.8.1.jar) in ant lib folder  (ANT_HOME/lib) and use a 
&gt;  &gt; &lt;classpath /&gt; with all the ant lib jars added to it.
&gt;  &gt; 
&gt;  &gt; This works when I run the build script through ant from command line.
&gt;  &gt; The same build script will not work from within Eclipse. Not sure why.
&gt;  
&gt;  It could be that when you&#39;re running ant from within Eclipse, you&#39;re not
&gt;  using the ant you think you&#39;re using.  That&#39;s happened to me before.  By
&gt;  default, Eclipse uses its own ant, which has its own ant/lib, which
&gt;  doesn&#39;t come with the JUnit jars in it.  My solution was to configure
&gt;  Eclipse to use the same ant I used from outside Eclipse.
